parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Failure Due to Poor Design and Heat-Induced Fluid Boil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when riding on inclines or in heavy traffic conditions.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not engage the rear brake
the brake pedal must be depressed all the way down to engage
the rear brake fluid reservoir is discolored
and the bike rolls backward despite applying the rear brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift drum can cause the transmission to pop out of gear, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds.
symptoms: The transmission pops out of first and second gear when under hard acceleration
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting
